==Release history==
Perry released a video teaser for "Roar" on August 2, 2013 along with an announcement that the American release was scheduled for August 12<ref>{{cite journal| title=Katy Perry Posts 'Roar' Teaser, Announces Single Release Date | journal=Billboard | date=August 2, 2013 | accessdate=March 2014 | last=Gocobachi | first=Pam | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5638070/katy-perry-posts-roar-teaser-announces-single-release-date}}</ref> with a subsequent release to [[Contemporary hit radio|mainstream radio]] on August 13.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20130814082751/http://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases |archivedate=August 14, 2013 |title=Top 40/M Future Releases |publisher=All Access Music Group}}</ref> However, the song debuted two days earlier than expected by 'leaking' on August 10.<ref>{{cite web| date=August 10, 2013 | title=Katy Perry's New Single 'Roar' Leaks: Listen| url=http://news.radio.com/2013/08/10/katy-perry-roar-leak/ | first=Courtney E. | last=Smith }}</ref> The UK release was originally scheduled for September 8, but on August 30 Perry announced the release date would be moved up to September 1.<ref>{{cite web | title=Katy Perry Brings Roar's UK Release Date Forward | url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/katy-perry/news/katy-perry-brings-roars-uk-release-date-forward | accessdate=March 2014 | publisher=MTV}}</ref>

